<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Taunt2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Taunt,</orth> vb. to scoff, to mock; 1) trans.: <cit><quote>did not her kitchen-maid rail, t. and scorn me?</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4, 77</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 109</bibl> (Qq <emph>--ed, scorned and baited at;</emph> Ff <emph>baited, scorned and stormed at</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 134</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 111</bibl>. 2) absol.: <cit><quote>I'll write to him a very --ing letter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.134" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 134</bibl></cit>. 3) with <emph>at</emph>: <cit><quote>to t. at slackness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.7.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 7, 28</bibl></cit> (cf. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 109</bibl>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>